...of your apprenticeship. You have learned the arts of crafting wands, crafting with Essentia and Vis, even combining the two into Arcane Infusion. You have learned about Warp and Taint, Nodes and centi-Vis... and yet, surely, there must be so much more to discover still.

It's time to say goodbye to your mentor. He has helped you a great deal, but you wish to continue beyond where he stopped. Which reminds you... he said that when your apprenticeship with him was over, you would be ready to face Warp. Travel to the world between and confront who- or whatever has been trying to draw you there. Are you truly ready? You must confess you don't §ofeel§r ready...

One last time you ask your mentor for advice, and he tells you that you are indeed ready to open the path, if you manage to find it. Traversing it, though? That will depend on your wits.

You thank your mentor, one last time, and wish him...actually, question: What §ois§r the guy's name anyhow? You never thought to ask before.

With the most bemused smile you've seen on him yet your mentor, somewhat belatedly, introduce himself as Ifnkovhgroghprm. And wishes you the best, as well.

...Ifnkovhgroghprm? Geez. If you become half as good at magic as that guy is at articulating you'll be the best mage who has ever lived...
